  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various methods and strategies, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Regulations\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Mandating transaction monitoring and record-keeping\n\n2. Law Enforcement Investigations\n- Financial crime units specializing in tracing illicit funds\n- Collaboration between national and international agencies\n- Advanced forensic accounting techniques\n\n3. International Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated investigations targeting transnational criminal networks\n\n4. Legal Prosecution\n- Criminal charges for money laundering activities\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- Significant financial penalties\n\n5. Technology-Based Detection\n- Advanced data analytics\n- Machine learning algorithms\n- Transaction pattern recognition systems\n\n6. Regulatory Compliance\n- Strict reporting requirements\n- Regular audits of financial institutions\n- Substantial penalties for non-compliance\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering schemes through multi-layered legal and technological strategies.",
